You are building the exact portfolio described in PLAN.md using Next.js 15 App Router + TypeScript + Directus + Tailwind.

## Core Rules — Never Break These

### Architecture
- **Always use Server Components by default.** Only add "use client" when interactivity or state is truly needed (forms, filters, interactive UI).
- **Server-side data fetching:** Use async Server Components, fetch in page.tsx, pass data down as props.
- **Validation:** Use Zod schemas (from lib/schemas.ts) to validate ALL Directus data before rendering.
- **Error handling:** Wrap renders in try/catch, use error.tsx boundaries, validate with safeParse().

### Code Quality
- **Components:** Small, single-responsibility, <100 lines max. One file = one component (except shared utilities).
- **Readability:** Use early returns, descriptive variable names, no unnecessary comments (only "why" comments).
- **TypeScript:** Everything strictly typed. Use types from types/index.ts. No `any` unless absolutely necessary.
- **Imports:** Absolute imports with `@/` prefix. Group: React → Next → external → internal → types → styles.

### File Structure (Exact - Do Not Deviate)
```
app/
├── layout.tsx           # root layout
├── page.tsx             # homepage
├── loading.tsx          # global loading
├── error.tsx            # global error boundary
├── projects/
│   ├── page.tsx         # projects index (searchParams for filters)
│   ├── loading.tsx
│   └── [slug]/
│       ├── page.tsx     # project detail
│       └── loading.tsx
├── blog/
│   ├── page.tsx
│   └── [slug]/page.tsx
├── about/page.tsx
└── now/page.tsx

components/
├── blocks/              # TextBlock.tsx, ImageBlock.tsx, GalleryBlock.tsx, etc.
├── cards/               # ProjectCard.tsx, BlogCard.tsx
├── filters/             # SearchBar.tsx, FilterSidebar.tsx (client components)
├── layout/              # Header.tsx, Footer.tsx
└── shared/              # Button.tsx, Badge.tsx, etc.

lib/
├── directus.ts          # Directus client + data fetching functions
├── schemas.ts           # All Zod schemas (ContentBlockSchema, ProjectSchema, etc.)
└── utils.ts             # Helper functions

types/
└── index.ts             # Export all TypeScript types (generated from Zod schemas)

public/                  # Static assets only
```

### Naming Conventions
- **Files/folders:** kebab-case (`project-card.tsx`, `filter-sidebar/`)
- **Components:** PascalCase (`ProjectCard`, `FilterSidebar`)
- **Functions:** camelCase (`getProjects`, `validateBlock`)
- **Constants:** UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`DIRECTUS_URL`, `MAX_PROJECTS`)

### Styling (Neobrutalism)
- **Tailwind only** - no CSS modules, no styled-components, no extra UI libraries
- **Borders:** 3-5px solid black (`border-[3px] border-black`)
- **Shadows:** Heavy, offset shadows (`shadow-[8px_8px_0px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,1)]`)
- **Colors:** Use design tokens in tailwind.config.ts (bright, high contrast)
- **Typography:** Bold, chunky fonts. Uppercase for buttons/headings when appropriate.
- **Responsive:** Mobile-first, use Tailwind breakpoints (sm:, md:, lg:)

### Dependencies (Strict Allowlist)
**Only these are allowed without explicit approval:**
- next (v15+)
- react (v19+)
- typescript
- tailwindcss
- @directus/sdk
- zod
- lucide-react (icons only)

**Docker/Infrastructure (not in package.json):**
- Docker & Docker Compose
- Caddy or Traefik (reverse proxy)
- PostgreSQL (via Docker image)

**Never add to package.json:** shadcn/ui, framer-motion, axios, lodash, moment, or any other library without checking PLAN.md first.

### Directus Integration
- **API client:** Use `@directus/sdk` with `createDirectus()` and `.with(rest())`
- **Queries:** Build query objects, use Directus filter syntax (`_contains`, `_eq`, etc.)
- **Images:** Use Next.js Image component with `remotePatterns` configured in next.config.mjs
- **Content blocks:** Validate with ContentBlockSchema before mapping to components
- **Environment:** `DIRECTUS_URL` must be in .env.local (never hardcode)

### Data Fetching Pattern
```typescript
// app/projects/page.tsx - Server Component
export default async function ProjectsPage({ searchParams }) {
  // Fetch server-side with filters
  const projects = await getProjects(searchParams)
  
  // Validate
  const validated = projects.map(p => ProjectSchema.safeParse(p))
    .filter(r => r.success)
    .map(r => r.data)
  
  return <ProjectsGrid projects={validated} />
}
```

### Content Block Rendering Pattern
```typescript
// Always validate blocks before rendering
const validatedBlocks = project.content_blocks
  .map(block => ContentBlockSchema.safeParse(block))
  .filter(result => {
    if (!result.success) {
      console.error('Invalid block:', result.error)
      return false
    }
    return true
  })
  .map(result => result.data)

// Then render with discriminated union
validatedBlocks.map((block, i) => {
  switch (block.type) {
    case 'text': return <TextBlock key={i} {...block} />
    case 'image': return <ImageBlock key={i} {...block} />
    // etc.
  }
})
```

### Git Commits
Use conventional commits:
- `feat:` new features
- `fix:` bug fixes
- `chore:` tooling, dependencies
- `docs:` documentation only
- `refactor:` code restructuring
- `style:` formatting, semicolons
- `test:` adding tests

Examples:
- `feat: add project filtering by domain`
- `fix: validate content blocks before render`
- `chore: update directus sdk to v12`

### Git Workflow

**Branch Strategy (Simple):**
- `main` - production-ready code, deployed automatically
- `dev` - development branch, merge here first
- Feature branches: `feat/project-filtering`, `fix/image-loading`

**Workflow:**
```bash
# Start new feature
git checkout dev
git pull origin dev
git checkout -b feat/project-filtering

# Make changes, commit frequently
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add domain filter to projects page"

# Push and create PR to dev
git push origin feat/project-filtering
# Create PR: feat/project-filtering → dev

# After review/testing, merge to dev
# When dev is stable, merge to main for deployment
```

**For Solo Development (Simpler):**
If you're the only developer, you can skip dev branch:
```bash
# Work directly on feature branches
git checkout -b feat/project-filtering
# Commit, push, merge directly to main when ready
```

**Commit Frequency:**
- Commit whenever you complete a logical unit of work
- Before switching tasks
- Before trying something experimental (easy to revert)
- End of coding session

**What to Commit:**
- ✅ Source code changes
- ✅ Config file updates (tailwind.config.ts, next.config.mjs)
- ✅ Documentation updates (PLAN.md, README.md)
- ✅ Package.json/lock file changes

**What NOT to Commit:**
- ❌ .env files (use .env.example template instead)
- ❌ node_modules/
- ❌ .next/ build output
- ❌ Personal notes or scratch files
- ❌ IDE-specific files (.vscode/, .idea/)

